onCreate

public void onCreate(SQLiteDatabase db)
Runs when the database doesn't already exist. Creates two tables: PEOPLE_TABLE for permanent entry storage and TEMP_TABLE for temporary storage during network XML parsing.

onUpgrade

public void onUpgrade(SQLiteDatabase db,
                      int oldVersion,
                      int newVersion)
Runs if the DATABASE_VERSION of the app code if higher than that of the stored database. Can move around data, rename fields, or whatever is necessary to ensure compatibility while saving existing data. Since this is the first version of the database, it does nothing.
